        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 4:16PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Morton, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Morton, Forest, and Forkville around 420 PM CDT.
Hillsboro around 425 PM CDT.
Harperville around 435 PM CDT.
Steele around 445 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
